==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[fasciculus]], a diminutive of [[fascis]] "bundle"

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈfæsɪkəl/}}
*{{audio|en-us-fascicle.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
# A [[bundle]]
# A [[section]] a book, that because of its length, is [[issue]]d in [[part]]s so that the information may be made available to the public as soon as possible.
# {{anatomy}}: A bundle of [[skeletal]] [[muscle]] [[fiber]]s surrounded by [[connective tissue]].
# {{anatomy}}: Specialized muscle fibers in the [[heart]] which transmit electrical [[impulse]]s from the [[AV node]] to the [[Purkinje_fibers]].
# {{botany}}: A [[cluster]] of [[flower]]s or [[leaf|leaves]], such as the bundles of the thin leaves (or needles) of [[pine]]s.
# {{botany}}: A [[discrete]] bundle of [[vascular]] [[tissue]].

